    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1881530157" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1881530157" />
    <a title="Shawn Deal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7027982-shawn-deal"><img alt="Shawn Deal" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547589212p2/7027982.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1881530157?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shawn Deal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shawn Deal" href="/user/show/7027982-shawn-deal">Shawn Deal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7027982-shawn-deal?shelf=history">history</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1881530157" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer392738831230705417">I have read many biographies over the last many years, especially on the Presidents, and this one is one of the best. Chronicling the rise in power of Theordore Roosevelt, this book essentially starts with his childhood and goes to the moment he finds out that he has become president through assassination. With some amazing details, this book goes through every position he has until Presidency and through all the major decisions he has to make personally and professionally. The reader really get</span>
  <span id="freeText392738831230705417" style="display:none">I have read many biographies over the last many years, especially on the Presidents, and this one is one of the best. Chronicling the rise in power of Theordore Roosevelt, this book essentially starts with his childhood and goes to the moment he finds out that he has become president through assassination. With some amazing details, this book goes through every position he has until Presidency and through all the major decisions he has to make personally and professionally. The reader really gets the sense of who this man is, and what events made him into the man he is. I cannot say enough great things about this book. This is the first of a planned trilogy, the second Theodore Rex, will concentrate on his Prediency and third will discuss the rest of his life. Can't wait to read these. </span>
  <a data-text-id="392738831230705417" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


